Kaas and Bruch. Ice thickness 19". Snow cover none.  Max recorded depth is 46'.
Rain 3-4 in. 8/31 with heavy runoff- really effects clarity
Ice off 3/15/90- secchi set new record!
Best clarity yet! some green algae on bottom
Green water lasted 10 days to 2 weeks.
Start of algae bloom- best depth for July.
Lake level not as high as last year.  Ice off 3-31-94.
Low algae levels this year.  Green is gone.
Ice off 3/18/95.  No run-off this year to raise lake level.
Absolutely perfect.  Calm- no high winds to stir it up lake superior style.  Added 2' of oar for record 32'.
High winds from east.  Finally a clear day.
Department of Natural Resources notified.  Hot weather during ( ) off.  150-200 large carp died starting July 29 for 4-5 days.  They were floating to the surface.
8/9/95 heavy run-off from heavy rains.  Lake level up 8-9" in one day.
Been green in color for a week.
Ice off 2/26/98- earliest we remember.  High wind and rain.
A beautiful summer lots of swimming great weekends.
High winds. great amount of turbulence.
5/18/1999: level 35.8. Ice off 3/17/99. not much snow cover this winter.
On 9/12 the gauge was 32.5 and there was 2.75 inches of rain on that monday.
Ice off on 4/7.  Long winter of snow coverage on ice.
The water temperature is 74 degrees and a six week long algae bloom is finally finished.
Cold May and June and a great July and August.
Great summer- warm- dry and no mosquitos.
We have numerous sightings of zebra mussels.
Cold summer - little swimming or boating.
lots of weeds exposed in 4-12' partially because of loss of water 17"
beautiful summer- great weather- I believe this is record low water since I started recording
Ice off 3/24/2006.  Poor thin ice winter.  Little fishing and winter activities.
very windy- sunny- received materials late- 80F
Last two week - Eurasian Milfoil letting loose by the roots and floating to the surface.  Very warm water temps.
Lots of weeds this fall at surface level 5'-12' of water.
Ice on mid Jan 2007.  Ice off 3/25/2007.  They were fishing from a boat New Years weekend.
Zebra mussels are working.  34 is a record for depth.  I ran out of oar.  Clear water.  Lots of weeds already.
Heavy Rain 4" last two days high water peak 39.75"
Ice off March 24- 2010. Beautiful- clear water.
Water is low. Lots of weeds.
Golden Lake Association purchases their own D/O meter with temp. reading by HACII
ice off 3/12/2012- not very much ice cover on for very long
Ice off 4/11/13. Eurasian milfoil treatment first week of June '13.
John Sipos' personal highest recorded water level reading
Ice off 3/25/2015- low secchi reading for May
(Secci record depth): "Lake deep at this location and with this water depth less than 45"
